**SPECIAL CONTAINMENT PROCEDURES:** All communication by Groups of Interest regarding SCP-9206 is to be forwarded to Dr. Mary Jupiter.

Site-3 personnel are discouraged from allowing Avisocc-related activities to affect the quality of their work.

------

**DESCRIPTION:** SCP-9206 is a spontaneous phenomenon biannually affecting 67% of England's adult Avifauna.


Avians affected by SCP-9206[[footnote]] Henceforth referred to as SCP-9206-1 [[/footnote]] will show the following anomalous effects for the next 10 months after being affected:

* An abnormally high cognitive function.
* Increased dexterity and bone density
* A desire to converge in specific locations along with their respective species.
* Innate knowledge of POI-9206's location.


Approximately 90 minutes after being affected by SCP-9206, said avians will attempt to migrate towards POI-9206. If contact is successful, all SCP-9206-1 instances will collect the closest spherical object and attempt to replicate a season of Association Football.

POI-9206 is an adult female Sagittarius serpentarius[[footnote]] Secretary bird. [[/footnote]], that is presumably the cause of all SCP-9206 events. POI-9206 is sapient as well as capable of communication in English, possessing a large amount of knowledge in both business theory and sports science. POI-9206 designates itself as the "manager" of all SCP-9206 events, often grouping SCP-9206-1 instances into teams with appropriate captains and substitutes, along with leading them towards wide patches of grass.





------



**ADDENDUM-I:** History



The first recorded SCP-9206 event took place on 4/5/2012, causing large commotion among England's populace due to the disappearance of pets and overcrowding of public spaces. Following immediate public outcry, the Department of Misinformation approved the implementation of a media blackout coupled with a nationwide amnesticization campaign for the time being. Eventually approving the deployment of MTF Lionel-3 "Fisher's Wit" to investigate further.

However, while approaching a group of SCP-9206-1 instances in a forest near Manchester, the task force was intercepted by a Global Occult Coalition Strike Team attempting to terminate the instances. This confrontation escalated into a firefight after a series of disagreements caused by a lack of information regarding the anomaly and the potential appearance of containment teams in the area.

A ceasefire would only be declared after instances began to replicate practice drills using nearby bullet casings. Seemingly ignoring the altercation entirely.

This behavioral change, along with diplomatic efforts by site command, would convince the strike team to temporarily halt liquidation attempts until further information was gathered.


Following the establishment of a temporary containment perimeter in the area, POI-9206 approached Agent Franklin Lang with a slab of carved wood stating:

[[=]]

[[div class="jotting"]]

fİve HunDrEd dOlaR peR Tiket pLs

[[/div]]
[[/=]]


This would result in the following interaction:

[[collapsible show="+ Open Transcript" hide="- Close Transcript"]]

[[div class="blockquote"]]

**<Start Log>**

//Agent Barry stares at the sign.//

**Barry:** W-what?

**POI-9206:** Your fee.

**Barry:** You can speak?

**POI-9206:** Duh, didn't think you'd hear me over all that ruckuse though. There better not be any blood on the pitch.

**Barry:** Well, uhh, we stopped that. Thankfully, no blood was spilled.

**POI-9206:** Mhmm.

//5 Seconds of silence.//

**Barry:** So, what about the sign?

**POI-9206:** I doubt that you are either blind or deaf, intruder. Provide your payment if you wish to observe. With haste, please. I'm a busy woman.

**Barry:** I don't-, [//sigh//] the hell is going on here?

**POI-9206:** Isn't it obvious? We are in the middle of the season-opener. And I would very much appreciate it if you could not take my attention hostage for long.

**Barry:** Oh come on! Soccer? Really?

**POI-9206:** The ritual of Avisocc is not something to take lightly. No, it's a method of dominance and self-expression. Quite profitable overseas too, I might add.

**Barry:** You have a weird-ass name for it, too? [//sigh//] [[size 0.8em]] I should've just stayed in Zeta-9...[[/size]]

**POI-9206:** May the Forebearer curse thyne foul tounge! I shall take my leave!

//Agent Barry runs back to Lieutenant Zimmerman, quickly returning to POI-9206 after a short exchange.//

**POI-9206:** Ugh, just leave us alone already.

//POI-9206 turns and begins to walk towards the SCP-9206-1 instances.//

**Barry:** Will this be enough to cover me?

//Agent Barry hands POI-9206 a 200 pound bill.//

**POI-9206:** [//Scoffs//] These aren't even dollars!

**Barry:** We're in England.

//Prolonged silecne.//

**POI-9206:** You leave after the second half...

**<End Log>**

[[/div]]
[[/collapsible]]



Sustained negotiations with POI-9206 would continue for two months after Agent Barry's initial departure from the area, leading to the eventual establishment of the International Association Parasport Federation (IAPF), an organizational committee created to peacefully resolve conflicts between Groups of Interest by forming official sports leagues.


------

**ADDENDUM-II:** Rule Overview



After the formation of the IAPF, the sport of Avisocc was officially recognized as an anomalous branch of Football and sanctioned with the following rules in cooperation with POI-9206:


* All games will be played with 42 players total, with 10 substitutes.
* All games will be played in 60 minutes with two 30-minute halves.
* The ball must not be made of shiny materials.
* Only goalkeepers may use their wings or beak to touch the ball.
* No player may fly while carrying the ball for more than 3 seconds.
* All official bets on Avisocc matches by registered Groups of Interest are to be made on Kalshi.[[footnote]] "Its convenient" -POI-9206 [[/footnote]]



------



