**ADDENDUM-IV:** Internal Text Logs

The following is a contextually relevant exchange between two staff members involved with SCP-9206 research.



[[div class="text-container-wrap"]]

[[div class="text-container"]]


[[div class="sent"]]
[[span class="text"]]Heyy Pearly... [[/span]]
[[/div]]


[[div class="recv"]]
[[span class="text"]]Why are you not in caps lock. [[/span]]
[[/div]]

[[div class="sent"]]
[[span class="text"]]What? [[/span]]
[[/div]]

[[div class="recv"]]
[[span class="text"]]Just send me the funeral address.[[/span]]
[[/div]]

[[div class="sent"]]
[[span class="text"]] It's not like that! [[/span]]
[[/div]]


[[div class="recv"]]
[[span class="text"]] I'm surprised you didn't call me about arrangements sooner.[[/span]]
[[/div]]

[[div class="sent"]]
[[span class="text"]]Look, I know it's a bit sudden, but could you cover my gas for like the next two days? You know how it is, money dries up quickly in this economy,  yknow? I mean, the highly intellectual conversations of the birby's aren't easy to put on paper, yknow?[[/span]]
[[/div]]


[[div class="recv"]]
[[span class="text"]]...[[/span]]
[[/div]]


[[div class="sent"]]
[[span class="text"]] Y'know? [[/span]]
[[/div]]

[[div class="recv"]]
[[span class="text"]]Don't even start.[[/span]]
[[/div]]

[[div class="sent"]]
[[span class="text"]] Oh come on! [[/span]]
[[/div]]

[[div class="recv"]]
[[span class="text"]] Vil, do YOU know how hard things are in the psych wing this week? Mary thinks about jumping every other hour! And those no-name goi's aren't gonna stop leeching off our sport any time soon. Go ask the ducks or whatever.
[[/span]]
[[/div]]



[[div class="sent"]]
[[span class="text"]] "Our", sport? [[/span]]
[[/div]]


[[div class="recv"]]
[[span class="text"]]Well yea.[[/span]]
[[/div]]



[[div class="sent"]]
[[span class="text"]]When was the last time our shining stars took formation, let alone a single point off the goddamn Geese against weed?! FYI, the betting list is public! And you aren't exactly a saint of financial responsibility! [[/span]]
[[/div]]



[[div class="recv"]]
[[span class="text"]]God forbid I support my own organization! Maybe you should try to support your budget before begging me! Also, what does this have to do with anything? Go ask Albert if you wanna save the team or whatever.
[[/span]]
[[/div]]



[[div class="sent"]]
[[span class="text"]]Don't pressure me! I need to vent here! The point is, Pearly, that the team is a bunch of fraudulent bums! Why did we make a sport we can't even play! For fucks sake I haven't seen the Insurgency do this much damage to morale during raids...[[/span]]
[[/div]]


[[div class="sent"]]
[[span class="text"]]Ps: You owe me donut money from March, so yeah.[[/span]]
[[/div]]



[[div class="recv"]]
[[span class="text"]] You know what? Maybe you're right, the Foundation can't play Birdball for shit...
[[/span]]
[[/div]]


[[div class="sent"]]
[[span class="text"]]I know right?[[/span]]
[[/div]]


[[div class="recv"]]
[[span class="text"]] So, how about we play something else?
[[/span]]
[[/div]]



[[div class="sent"]]
[[span class="text"]]W H A T[[/span]]
[[/div]]


[[div class="recv"]]
[[span class="text"]] Have the Quackmobile ready, I'll get the gas.
[[/span]]
[[/div]]


[[div class="sent"]]
[[span class="text"]]Yes ma'am! [[/span]]
[[/div]]

[[/div]]
[[/div]]


------








[[div class="modal"]]

+ PROJECT PROPOSAL-F.42

++ "Hide-n-Seekers"

**Proposed by:** Dr. Pearl N. Langstrum
**Proposed to:** Dir. Albert Ezekiel, Site-3
------



Due to the reported and significant drop in staff morale caused by recent developments following the establishment of the IAFP, I propose a 3-step solution to increase favorable relations with certain Groups of Interest, as well as removing excessive Foundation spending. My proposal is as follows:


**STEP-1:** Introduce educational courses related to financial responsibility aimed at LVL-3 or lower personnel.

**STEP-2:** Increase the annual budget of the Psychiatry wing.

**STEP-3:** Utilize [[[https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/scp-9386 |SCP-9386]]] as a player in Team Foundation.[[footnote]] A sapient female rook capable of translocating itself up to approximately 100 meters away from its current position when not observed.[[/footnote]]

------

Proposal Status: **##green| Begrudgingly Accepted##**

[[/div]]

------

**ADDENDUM-IV:** Interview Log



[[div class="blockquote"]]
[[=]]
++++ **- SESSION 9386-01 -**
[[/=]]
**Date:** 25/9/2012
**Counsellor:** Dr. Pearl N. Langstrum
**Patient:** SCP-9386
----
**<Start Log>**

//Dr. Langstrum enters SCP-9386's enclosure with a small gold ball in her hand.//

//She approaches SCP-9386, who is currently chasing a beetle.//

**Dr. Langstrum:** Hiii, Greg...

**SCP-9386:** My name! You remembered Greg!

**Dr. Langstrum:** Don't mention it, it's what friends do.

**SCP-9386:** Well, Greg doesn't mind if you forget, I'll keep reminding you!

**Dr. Langstrum:** That's wonderful, Greg.

//Dr. Langstrum kneels down.//

**Dr. Langstrum:** So, how are you today?

**SCP-9386:** EXCITED!

//SCP-9386 starts hopping around in a circular motion.//

**SCP-9386:** You smell like beetles!


//Dr. Langstrum sniffs her sleeve.//


**Dr. Langstrum:** Ah, well. I'm sure it's a familiar smell to you.

**SCP-9386:** It is! Not as familiar as-

**SCP-9386:** Wait...

**SCP-9386:** *Gasp* DID YOU COME TO PLAY HIDE AND SEEK!?

**Dr. Langstrum:** That's a complicated question.


//Dr. Langstrum moves to sit atop a wooden log nearby.//


**Dr. Langstrum:** I've come to teach you a new game! Yaaay!


//SCP-9386 appears dissatisfied.//

**SCP-9386:** I don't wanna play another game, I wanna play HIDE and SEEK!

**Dr. Langstrum:** Well, what if I told you that this game was....A NEW KIND OF HIDE AND SEEK!

//SCP-9386 cocks its head back.//

**SCP-9386:** A new form of Hide  Seek? No such thing could exist. And if it did, I would know as someone with a PhD in Hideseekian Studies.

//Dr. Langstrum snaps her fingers.//


**Dr. Langstrum:** That's just it, Greg! This game is sooo secret that it's always hiding its own existence.


**SCP-9386:** Wait..but that would mean I'm currently IN a game of Hide and Seek!

**Dr. Langstrum:** Exactly, Greg!

//Dr. Langstrum removes the golden sphere from her pocket, showing it to SCP-9386.//


**Dr. Langstrum:** This little thing is the key to winning the game. You try to put it inside a net along with 40 others! But you can only use your feet.

**SCP-9386:** Like a hide-and-seek treasure hunt?

**Dr. Langstrum:** It's much more complicated than that, there's tactics and strategy and passing the ball to others, et cetera.


**SCP-9386:** What.


**Dr. Langstrum:** Hmm?


**SCP-9386:** That makes no sense. If everyone can already see the ball, then no one's hiding or seeking anything! And that's booooringgg!

**Dr. Langstrum:** Think of it like this, you're hiding the ball from the other seeker's legs while you try to score a goal. And I know just how much you love hiding! So surely a Hide and Seek champion such as yourself can see the appeal!

**SCP-9386:** That sounds like a rather contrived explanation for something quite unseekian.


//Prolonged silence.//


**Dr. Langstrum:** I-...

//Continued silence.//


**Dr. Langstrum:** I'll give you a shiny spoon if you play.

**<End Log>**
[[/div]]

------

