------

**ADDENDUM-V:** Offers

The following is a list of communications by various Groups of Interest in the last month regarding Project "Hide-n-Seekers".

------

[[div class="warning"]]

**Subject:** Offer for the Permanent Transfer of SCP-9386.

**Date:** 17/10/2012

**From:** Legal Department / G.O.C Undersecretary General Office


**To:** Senior Researcher Mary Jupiter


Dear Madam, we write on behalf of the Global Occult Coalition International Avisocc Club to make a formal offer for the permanent transfer of the registration rights of SCP-9386, currently registered with your club. The player is a central midfielder of intermediate age with a contract expiring on 30 June 2030. Our offer is as follows:


**Transfer Fee  Guaranteed / Base Fee:** £100,000,000 (one-hundred million pounds sterling)  

**Payment Structure:**  £50,000,000 payable within 7 days of receipt of the International Transfer Certificate (ITC) and successful completion of the medical.  


**Sell-On Clause:**

We propose a 30% sell-on clause on any future permanent transfer fee (net of any add-ons) received by our club if the player is sold to another club.


We believe this represents a very competitive proposal for the player and look forward to your positive response at your earliest convenience. Please do not hesitate to contact us if you require any further information or wish to discuss the terms.

Yours sincerely,  D.C. Al Fine
Club Secretary / Director of Avisocc Operations
Fivefold Phalanx Football Club
Email: legal@fivefoldphalanxac.com



[[/div]]

------

[[div class="email2"]]
[[div class="tofrom2"]]
**To:** ##9538a5|foundation@scp_outmail.██##
**From:** ##9538a5|ip.office@drwondertainment.██##
**Date Sent:** 17/11/2012
**Subject:** Re: Play Fair Please
[[/div]]
------
Good evening.

I am Carraway Rothwell, as Dr. Wondertainment's representative chair in the IAPF, I hereby request an emergency summit to discuss an overhaul in our official rules. We believe that using outside anomalous methods to gain an unfair advantage over other teams, constitutes both a breach of sportsmanship and financial fraud.


Learn to take a loss, for God's sake.

[[/div]]

------

[[div style="background: url(/local--files/3rd-vesta-donation/MCF-7.png) center center no-repeat ; float: center; border: solid 4px #6bab30; width: 560px; padding: 1px 15px; margin: 30px 10px 10px 20px; font-family: sansationregular, serif; background-color: #fff; box-shadow: 0 1px 3px rgba(0,0,0,.2);"]]
[[=]]
+ [[span style="color:#6BAB30;"]]EMERGENCY BULLETIN[[/span]]
[[span style="color:#6BAB30;"]]ARRIVED: 17/11/2012 6:07 PM Birmingham, United Kingdom[[/span]]
[[/=]]


We would like to congratulate the Foundation on its recent successes in this month's Avisocc season. The team's performance as of late is an inspirational story of resilience that both of our missions can relate to.

With that said, we hope that you will contribute the new funds gained from these victories for a proper cause, including our Avian wildfile preservation project in South Africa.


Sincerely,

- Mission watch external, Oceanian Headquarters



[[/div]]

------

